cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on evaluating people's perception of virtual humans.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the dataset used in the analysis contains pedestrian emotions and personalities detected using Computer Vision techniques.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the virtual humans were visualized and analyzed based on their geometric features.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the emotions and personalities of the virtual humans were detected using Pattern Recognition techniques.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the analysis involves video sequences of virtual humans.
